product_name: GarnierSkinActive Micellar Cleansing Water and Makeup Remover with Salicylic Acid
summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsCruelty FreeVeganSustainable PackagingCleanse & remove makeup with Garnier SkinActive Micellar Cleansing Water and Makeup Remover with Salicylic Acid. Its micellar tech purifies & refreshes skin.
details: DetailsBenefitsCleanses, removes makeup, mattifies skin all dayFrom America's Number 1 Micellar Water BrandItem 2634848How To UseSaturate a cotton pad with the Garnier Micellar Cleansing Water with Salicylic Acid.To remove eye makeup: Hold pad over closed eyes for a few seconds, then gently wipe away makeup without harsh rubbing.To cleanse skin and remove face makeup: Gently wipe pad all over face until skin is completely clean and makeup and impurities are removed.Use daily. No need to rinseIngredientsAqua / Water / Eau, Hexylene Glycol, Glycerin, Alcohol Denat., Poloxamer 184, Disodium Cocoamphodiacetate, Salicylic Acid, Disodium Edta, Myrtrimonium Bromide, Sodium Hydroxide, Ascorbyl Glucoside (F.I.L. reviews.headline: Surprisingly effective and I would buy it again
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This product does what it says. It's a nice Micellar water and I usually use it to clean my makeup. It nice removing things I don't get out with a cleanser during the shower. I don't think it did any wonders to my skin but overall I did find myself using it every day! Definitely appreciate Garnier as the mother of micellar cleansers! It sells by a fair price in drugstores and the scent it's not strong. I do usually rinse with water afterwards.

faceoff_positive.comments:
I recently tried Garnier's Micellar Water with Salicylic Acid, and I have to say, I'm impressed with how well it works for my skin. As someone with oily, acne-prone skin, I'm always on the lookout for products that can help with breakouts without being too harsh. This micellar water does a fantastic job of cleansing and treating my skin without over-drying it.

First off, the packaging is simple and effective. The bottle is clear, which makes it easy to see how much product is left, and the cap is secure enough to prevent spills, which is always a plus. The micellar water itself has a lightweight, watery texture and a very faint, pleasant scent that doesn't overpower or irritate my skin.

What really sets this apart from regular micellar water is the added salicylic acid. This ingredient is well-known for its ability to penetrate deep into pores and help exfoliate, so I was excited to see how it would work in a cleansing product. After using it for a few weeks, I've noticed that my skin feels cleaner and more refined. The salicylic acid helps keep breakouts at bay by gently exfoliating the skin without causing irritation, which can be a concern with stronger acne treatments. It's a nice balance‚Äîeffective but not harsh.

In terms of removing makeup, this micellar water performs just as well as any other I've used. It easily removes makeup, including waterproof mascara, without requiring much effort or rubbing. I find that it doesn't leave my skin feeling greasy or stripped, which is a big win in my book. It leaves my skin feeling refreshed, clean, and smooth.

One thing I appreciate about this product is that it doesn't cause any excessive dryness or tightness, even with the salicylic acid included. I was a little concerned that it might be too drying, but the formula is gentle enough for daily use. After using it consistently, my skin feels clearer, and I've noticed fewer breakouts, which is exactly what I hoped for.

Overall, I'm very pleased with Garnier's Micellar Water with Salicylic Acid. It's a great addition to my skincare routine, and it has become my go-to cleanser for both daily use and makeup removal. If you have oily or acne-prone skin, I highly recommend giving this a try‚Äîit's an effective, no-fuss product that delivers results.
faceoff_positive.headline: Effective Cleanser for Acne-Prone Skin

faceoff_negative.comments:
This product has been a great addition to my skincare routine, especially during that time of the month when I'm prone to breakouts. It effectively cleanses my skin, removes makeup, and helps control excess oil without leaving any residue. I did however have to use it sparingly during the winter as my skin was more dry and the salicylic acid contributed to it. The scent is mild, which I appreciate, and I love that the ingredients are cruelty-free.

However, the packaging was a big issue. My bottle arrived damaged‚Äîthe plastic cap was broken, and there was even a piece of plastic inside the liquid. The product box was also wet, and I lost about a quarter of the product during shipping. Garnier should consider sealing the top better to prevent leaks and damage.

Overall, the formula itself is great, and the price is affordable, but they really need to improve the packaging to avoid product loss and contamination.
faceoff_negative.headline: Effective but packaging needs improvement
